title: For Sale:  Original Carl Gustafs Swedish Mauser 6.5x55 w/ Bayonet M96 1916
postcontent:
This is an all original Swedish Mauser.  It was produced in 1916 and bears the famous "Carl Gustafs Stads Gevarsfaktori" ("Rifle Factory of Carl Gustaf's town") crest.  This one appears to be all original, and in excellent condition.  I have fired it and found it to be as accurate as the legend says it should be.  Also included is an original bayonet, although I do not believe that it came with the rifle.  On the left side of the receiver it has MB stamped before the serial number, which is 3907xx.  It has no rust that I can find and the stock is excellent.  The stock disc indicates that this has a 6.51mm bore with a condition 1 bore (good+) and no holdover needed with standard ammo.  This also has the M96 range card on the stock as well.

 I'll include a bag of approximately 40 primed brass that came with it that I never used.  I have shot Prvi Partizan brass in this rifle with great results.  

I will accept rifle trade offers too, plus or minus cash.  Not interested in AR-15s, sorry. A PSL-54C would be great, with cash added of course.  Something like a Suomi, or a Hipower.  For some reason I like odd guns, feel free to see if what you have is of interest to me.

Kinematic Drive™ SYSTEM
In its simplest term, kinetic energy is the energy of motion. The new Browning A5 makes better use of kinetic energy with its powerful, short recoil-operated Kinematic Drive System. Kinematic Drive harnesses recoil energy and converts it into the mechanical motion needed to operate the action. This concept is tried and true, and now perfected by the company that broke ground first with autoloading shotguns. The beauty of Kinematic Drive is the simplicity of design for consistent, reliable function with any load and under the full extremes of weather, temperature, moisture and grime. We believe the new Kinematic Drive is so reliable that the A5 is the first ever autoloading shotgun to carry a 100,000-round or five-year guarantee. This gun is designed to work, come hell or high water. Operation is clean because gases are sent out the barrel and away from the action. There’s also extreme load versatility. The extensively tested Kinematic Drive offers reliable performance with virtually all loads down to 1 ounce field loads with no adjustments.

title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson 4006 .40 Caliber semiautomatic pistol
location: Pioneer Square to Fremont, Seattle, Washington
postcontent:
Accurate and built like a tank. I only sell to buyers with a CURRENT WA CPL AND A CURRENT PICTURE ID. I submit a pistol transfer report to the state. This gun is in excellent mechanical condition. It shows signs of holster wear as a duty weapon.

From Wikapedia: It features a stainless steel frame and slide double-action, semi-automatic handgun with 4 inch barrel, slide mounted de-cock/safety and an 11-round staggered-column magazine. It was one of the new 3rd generation S&W semi-autos, designed with input from famed gunsmith Wayne Novak of Parkersburg, WV. The 4006 introduced the new .40 S&W cartridge and featured a wrap around one piece grip made of Xenoy versus the earlier standard 2 piece grip panels, as well as low profile 3 dot Novak sights. Various safety features include a safety lever, which blocked the firing pin from the hammer as well as a magazine safety, which kept the pistol from firing when no magazine was inserted. While a true double-action pistol, the firearm shares this magazine disconnect feature with Browning Hi-Power pistols: it cannot be fired without the magazine in place. This feature was developed to meet the needs of various law enforcement agencies interested in providing another level of safety for their officers. The Model 4006 has been used by many law enforcement agencies as a standard duty sidearm, including by the California Highway Patrol, California State Parks and Rec., and until recently, the Colorado State Patrol.

title: For Sale:  Finn M39 Mosin Nagant
postcontent:
If you're not familiar with the M39, it is arguably the best of all the Finn modified Mosin Nagants. The Finns adopted the Russian M91 when they split from Russia during the Revolution but quickly decided it needed changes for their use. Both the Army and the White Guard did their own versions until just before the 1939 Winter War. There are actually more Finn variants of the Mosin than there are Russian. The M39 was an effort to consolidate the best of all the modifications into one standardized rifle. The list of improvements to the M39 vs an M91 include...

 Unique stock produced from local arctic hardwood making it very durable and resistant to temp changes. Stock has loops for both normal and side sling attachment. Side sling is used by Ski and Cav troops.

 Action floated with shims.

 The Typical Finn 2 stage Trigger. 

 Windage adjustable front sight. 

 Improved rear sight.

 Dimpled magazine to improve feeding.

 This rifle is a 1968 build among those used by the Finnish Army for competition. Rifle is in Excellent condition, all numbers match, and includes sling and the Arsenal "hang tag" showing it was never issued. Also included is a black soft case. Please be aware that the Finns reused many parts from older rifles when producing all of their Mosin variants. Because of this most Finn Mosins show wear and pitting from before the remanufacturing process. 

 This rifle is no different. The receiver is 1901 production at the Russian Izzy arsenal. Think about that. This receiver predates The Sino-Russian war of 1903, The Russian Revolution, WW1, the Winter War of 1939, and WW2. (called the Continuation War by Finns) The Receiver could have been involved on the battle field of any or all of these. Trust me, it has signs of wear and neglect in its previous life. 

 These rifles can sell for over $600 but since this is a 1968 it doesnt command as high a price. I'm offering it for $350 with ZERO haggling. Cash only. No Trades, No Checks. First person to put cash in my hand owns it. Keith @ REDACTED anytime. If this ad is still up the rifle is still for sale.
